    "created_at": "2015-09-22T09:29:24Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-22T09:29:24Z",
    "body": "Okay. This comes from Chromium. Apparently, it’s implemented there such that the dragging property only has an effect when `frame: false` is set. But currently, when you set `frame: false`, you can’t get any of the new title bar look/behavior. The two API-s are a bit at odds with each other.\n\nI can think of several ways to solve this, would be interested in feedback before jumping on any of them.\n- Patch Chromium so that `-webkit-app-region: drag` works regardless of the window configuration. (Sometimes it would be useful to have draggable elements in framed windows as well?)\n- Modify the Electron window setup behavior such that if `title-bar-style: hidden`, this to Chromium also means that `frame:false`, yet the title bar (which is invisible, doesn’t take up window content space, but still shows traffic lights) is still drawn on the Electron side.\n"
  },
