    "created_at": "2015-09-24T18:10:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-24T18:10:25Z",
    "body": "There is another issue that was introduced at the same time that is proving to be really frustrating. Even with `frame: false` draggable regions are only draggable as long as the cursor stays inside them, so if you click and drag a window then it stops dragging when the cursor moves outside the bounds. \n\nThis essentially makes the feature useless in the last several releases.\n"
